videos.description: Yante Maten exits the game against Kentucky early in the first half with an apparent leg injury.
videos.headline: Georgia's Maten exits with leg injury

videos.description: Malik Monk drives to the basket and makes the scoop shot to extend Kentucky's slim lead over Georgia.
videos.headline: Monk gets the scoop shot to fall

videos.description: Kentucky's Malik Monk finds Bam Adebayo for the alley-oop dunk in transition in a close game against Georgia.
videos.headline: Monk lobs pass to Adebayo for dunk

videos.description: Georgia's J.J. Frazier makes the 3-pointer before the end of the first half against Kentucky.
videos.headline: Georgia hits buzzer-beater before halftime

videos.description: Kentucky's Malik Monk has his shot blocked by E'Torrion Wilridge, Monk and Georgia's Mike Edwards both receive technical fouls after the whistle.
videos.headline: Monk has shot blocked, gets fired up

videos.description: Georgia's Mike Edwards throws down the one-handed dunk in the tight game against Kentucky.
videos.headline: Edwards' huge dunk fires up home crowd for Georgia

videos.description: Georgia's J.J. Frazier makes the tough jumper before Kentucky's Mychal Mulder answers with the 3-pointer in the tight contest.
videos.headline: Kentucky and Georgia trading blows with back-to-back buckets

videos.description: Kentucky's Isaiah Briscoe and Georgia's Pape Diatta get tangled up after the whistle.
videos.headline: Things getting heated between Kentucky and Georgia

videos.description: J.J. Frazier collects the rebound and scores in transition to give Georgia one possession lead over Kentucky.
videos.headline: Missed layup leads to easy bucket for Georgia

videos.description: Georgia's Juwan Parker makes the tough layup in back and forth game against Kentucky.
videos.headline: Parker cuts into the lane and makes tough layup

videos.description: Georgia's J.J. Fraizer makes the layup late in the game against Kentucky.
videos.headline: Frazier's big night continues with layup

videos.description: Kentucky beats Georgia on the road in a close game to worsen the Bulldogs' chances of making the NCAA tournament.
videos.headline: Breaking down Kentucky's hard fought win over Georgia

videos.description: Despite 36 points from Georgia's J.J. Frazier, No. 13 Kentucky closes the game on a 9-2 run to win 82-77.
videos.headline: Kentucky squeaks by Georgia on road
